      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p><!-- BIOGHIST REQUIRED -->Born 1929 in Ellenville NY, he graduated from Bronx High School of Science in 1946. Later he received his BA from University of Arkansas, finally attending Columbia University School of the Arts finishing with his Ed.D. at Columbia University Teacher's College.  His adulthood was spent teaching theater in the NYC public school system, including City College, and working as a theater critic for The New York Tribune.</p>
         <p/>
      </bioghist>
